WEBVTT

00:01.710 --> 00:05.089
THE DRAGON: In a land of myth
and a time of magic,

00:05.173 --> 00:10.428
the destiny of a great kingdom
rests on the shoulders of a young boy.

00:10.511 --> 00:14.390
His name, Merlin.

00:27.737 --> 00:29.488
You know what you need
after a hard day's hunt?

00:29.572 --> 00:31.032
Sleep.

00:31.199 --> 00:33.451
A nice cold tankard of mead.

00:35.203 --> 00:37.455
Mead. (SPURS ON HORSE)

00:55.056 --> 01:00.061
No better place to measure the mood of
your people than the local tavern.

01:00.144 --> 01:02.730
This is one of those moments where |
tell you something isn't a good idea

01:02.813 --> 01:04.397
and you ignore me, isn't it?

01:04.482 --> 01:07.526
You're learning, Merlin.
Slowly, but you're learning.

01:08.236 --> 01:11.322
Now, remember, in here
you're not my servant.

01:11.405 --> 01:13.741
I'm just a simple peasant like
everyone else.

01:16.035 --> 01:18.204
Simple part's right.

01:18.287 --> 01:19.664
What?

01:19.747 --> 01:22.166
| said, the sun is very bright.

01:22.333 --> 01:24.168
Yeah. Yeah, it is.

01:24.252 --> 01:26.587
(BOISTEROUS TALKING)

01:34.804 --> 01:36.264
(RAUCOUS LAUGHTER)

01:37.306 --> 01:39.684
Afternoon. What'll it be?

01:40.351 --> 01:41.352
-Um...
-Mmm.

01:41.477 --> 01:43.521
You're an handsome fellow.

01:44.063 --> 01:46.399
Well, you wouldn't be
the first to say it.

01:46.482 --> 01:48.818
Oh, no, sorry.

01:48.901 --> 01:51.445
| was talking about your friend here.

01:53.698 --> 01:55.157
Him?

01:57.034 --> 01:58.411
Thank you.

01:59.078 --> 02:00.871
Two tankards of mead, please.

02:07.795 --> 02:11.132
| was wrong.
Coming here was a great idea.

02:11.215 --> 02:12.633
(DOOR OPENING)

02:15.011 --> 02:17.138
(ALL FALL SILENT)

02:21.309 --> 02:23.227
(TRAY CRASHING)

02:24.312 --> 02:26.272
Afternoon, Mary.

02:26.355 --> 02:28.065
Business looks good.

02:28.149 --> 02:29.692
We have our better days.

02:29.775 --> 02:32.445
| don't suppose you'd begrudge
me my share, then.

02:42.705 --> 02:44.540
-And the rest?
-That's all we got.

02:44.623 --> 02:45.875
I'll not ask again!

02:45.958 --> 02:47.835
ARTHUR: Take your hands off her.

03:00.598 --> 03:02.516
I'm gonna make you pay for that.

03:02.600 --> 03:04.393
(CHUCKLES) I'd like to see you try.

03:08.522 --> 03:09.690
(WHISTLING LOUDLY)

03:09.815 --> 03:11.275
(DOOR OPENING)

03:19.325 --> 03:24.288
You had to open your big mouth,
didn't you, Merlin?

03:24.372 --> 03:28.000
You two have got yourselves in a
bit of a pickle,

03:28.084 --> 03:29.418
haven't you?

03:29.835 --> 03:31.879
You should get out of here
while you have the chance.

03:33.464 --> 03:34.757
You're probably right.

03:44.975 --> 03:46.185
(GASPING)

03:55.111 --> 03:56.487
Arthur!

04:01.367 --> 04:03.661
Merlin! Behind you!

04:12.878 --> 04:14.630
(CASTING SPELL)

04:19.552 --> 04:20.803
(GLASS SHATTERING)

04:37.695 --> 04:39.321
Pass the jug, huh?

04:45.369 --> 04:46.495
What do they call you, then?

04:46.579 --> 04:49.165
-Merlin.
-Gwaine. Pleasure to meet you.

04:50.833 --> 04:52.376
Such a waste, huh?

05:04.221 --> 05:06.724
(SHOUTING LOUDLY)

05:13.105 --> 05:15.399
(GASPING)

05:25.284 --> 05:26.827
How is he?

05:28.162 --> 05:31.290
Not good. He's losing a lot of blood.

05:32.708 --> 05:34.084
(CROWD BOOING)

05:34.168 --> 05:36.253
If this man ever troubles you again,

05:36.337 --> 05:40.299
word is to be sent to Camelot.
Soldiers will be here within a day.

05:40.382 --> 05:42.259
How can you make a promise like that?

05:43.594 --> 05:45.012
Because I'm the King's son,

05:45.846 --> 05:47.014
Prince Arthur.

05:49.099 --> 05:50.476
Prince Arthur?

05:50.935 --> 05:52.978
MARY: Prince Arthur in my tavern?

05:54.355 --> 05:55.564
-Come on!
-CROWD: Yes!

06:47.491 --> 06:49.493
Merlin, fetch me some fresh water,

06:49.660 --> 06:51.370
towels, a needle, and silk thread.

06:51.495 --> 06:52.746
And honey?

06:52.830 --> 06:54.290
You're learning.

06:55.791 --> 06:57.585
Helps fight the infection.

06:58.252 --> 07:01.297
-Will he be all right?
-Providing he's strong.

07:01.839 --> 07:03.173
He's that, all right.

07:04.008 --> 07:05.676
The man saved my life, Gaius.

07:07.428 --> 07:09.430
He's to be given anything he needs.

07:15.227 --> 07:16.562
(COUGHING)

07:20.983 --> 07:22.109
(GROANING)

07:22.192 --> 07:23.319
(DOOR OPENING)

07:27.072 --> 07:28.741
What am I doing in this bed?

07:28.824 --> 07:30.534
You were wounded.

07:30.618 --> 07:33.245
Arthur wanted to make sure
you were treated by his physician.

07:33.329 --> 07:34.371
Arthur?

07:34.997 --> 07:36.373
Prince Arthur.

07:36.498 --> 07:38.208
You saved his life.

07:38.917 --> 07:42.004
If I'd known who he was,
| probably wouldn't have.

07:42.087 --> 07:43.964
(GROANING)

07:45.924 --> 07:47.259
He's a noble.

07:47.468 --> 07:49.928
-Yeah, but he's a good man.
-(GWAINE CHUCKLING)

07:50.262 --> 07:52.306
If you say so.

07:52.389 --> 07:53.766
You're a hero.

07:53.932 --> 07:55.517
The King wants to thank you,

07:55.601 --> 07:57.353
in person. (GASPING)

07:57.436 --> 07:59.355
Please, no.

08:00.356 --> 08:02.149
I've met a few kings.

08:02.232 --> 08:04.109
Once you've met one you've...
You've met them all.

08:04.193 --> 08:07.071
-He'll probably give you a reward.
-I'm not interested.

08:07.446 --> 08:08.614
Besides,

08:09.490 --> 08:10.741
I've got everything I need

08:11.867 --> 08:12.910
right here.

08:14.244 --> 08:15.746
Why did you help us?

08:15.829 --> 08:18.082
Your chances looked between
slim and none.

08:18.916 --> 08:23.003
[, uh... I guess I just kind of
like the look of those odds.

08:24.171 --> 08:25.297
(CHUCKLES)

08:26.215 --> 08:28.759
-How's Gwaine?
-Recovering.

08:29.176 --> 08:30.260
(HORSES APPROACHING)

08:32.763 --> 08:33.931
Who's that?

08:38.434 --> 08:40.979
Ah, Sir Darien.

08:41.813 --> 08:43.440
He's here for the melee.

08:43.982 --> 08:47.611
Oh, yeah. The tournament where the
knights ride around

08:47.695 --> 08:50.698
hitting each other with blunt weapons
for no good reason.

08:51.407 --> 08:52.825
A little more to it than that.

08:53.367 --> 08:54.535
Really?

08:54.618 --> 08:57.246
All I've ever seen is people getting
the seven bells knocked out of them

08:57.329 --> 09:00.124
so that the last man standing
can be called the winner.

09:00.207 --> 09:04.670
The melee is the ultimate test
of strength and courage.

09:05.337 --> 09:07.005
Are you sure we're talking
about the same thing?

09:07.089 --> 09:09.800
Well, I wouldn't expect you
to understand. You're not a knight.

09:09.925 --> 09:12.886
Oh, well, if it means
| don't get clobbered round the head,

09:12.970 --> 09:14.388
I'm glad of it.

09:14.471 --> 09:16.223
I'm afraid it doesn't.

09:17.933 --> 09:19.476
Ow!

09:20.144 --> 09:22.187
| need that lot cleaned by noon.

09:24.314 --> 09:25.566
(GROANING)

09:40.164 --> 09:44.376
The Stalorne blades,
just as you requested.

09:49.840 --> 09:51.175
EBOR: They're blunt.

09:51.258 --> 09:55.179
That is only how they appear.

09:57.514 --> 09:59.183
(BOTH LAUGHING)

09:59.266 --> 10:01.143
Why should you want such a weapon?

10:02.561 --> 10:05.355
That's none of your business, old man.

10:08.609 --> 10:10.027
You have the crystals?

10:10.694 --> 10:12.029
Money first.

10:30.672 --> 10:31.924
Not yet.

10:36.053 --> 10:42.392
(CASTING SPELL)

10:55.489 --> 10:59.827
The wearer of these crystals will be
able to take on the form

11:00.953 --> 11:03.247
of whoever's blood they touch.

11:04.289 --> 11:05.541
Thank you.

11:06.250 --> 11:07.584
(CHUCKLING) Thank you.

11:22.599 --> 11:23.684
Now what?

11:23.767 --> 11:29.857
Now, Ebor, we can take our revenge on
Prince Arthur of Camelot.

11:29.940 --> 11:31.650
(GUFFAWING LOUDLY)

11:35.988 --> 11:37.447
(PANTING)

11:42.160 --> 11:45.289
(CHURCH BELLS TOLLING)

12:23.535 --> 12:25.537
| believe this belongs to you.

12:25.996 --> 12:28.373
| don't think so. It's not my color.

12:28.457 --> 12:31.001
Ah, let us see.

12:35.631 --> 12:37.758
| bet you've got a whole bunch of those
to hand out.

12:37.841 --> 12:39.927
No. Yours is the only one.

12:40.010 --> 12:41.094
(CHUCKLES)

12:41.178 --> 12:42.721
I'm Gwaine.

12:45.182 --> 12:46.975
You haven't told me your name.

12:47.351 --> 12:49.394
You look like a princess to me.

12:49.478 --> 12:53.607
So it's probably something
like Sophia or... Or Esmeralda.

12:53.690 --> 12:57.194
That's it. Princess Esmeralda.

12:57.319 --> 12:59.279
Stop it. People are staring.

12:59.363 --> 13:00.822
Not until you tell me your name.

13:00.906 --> 13:02.407
It's Gwen.

13:02.532 --> 13:05.577
There. That wasn't so hard now, was it?

13:06.745 --> 13:10.457
Let me carry that. A princess shouldn't
have to lump her washing around.

13:10.540 --> 13:12.501
Unfortunately I'm not a princess.

13:12.584 --> 13:15.587
Ah, but you see, you are to me.

13:19.716 --> 13:22.302
-This isn't working, is it?
-No, not really.

13:22.386 --> 13:25.347
But I like that you tried
and that you know when to give up.

13:27.724 --> 13:30.727
You'd better have this, in case someone
else takes your fancy.

13:30.811 --> 13:32.104
I've only eyes for you.

13:32.187 --> 13:33.397
I'm sure.

13:48.537 --> 13:50.872
How much further would you say it is
to Camelot?

13:50.956 --> 13:54.001
Half a day's ride.
The journey is almost over.

13:54.084 --> 13:55.669
It is for you.

13:55.752 --> 13:57.462
Oswald!

14:05.679 --> 14:06.930
Dagr!

14:09.599 --> 14:10.767
(CHUCKLING)

14:15.772 --> 14:17.357
The crystals.

14:26.908 --> 14:29.619
(ENERGY PULSATING)

14:45.135 --> 14:46.470
You look good, Dagr.

14:46.553 --> 14:47.971
Sir Oswald.

14:48.263 --> 14:49.306
Sorry, Sire.

14:49.931 --> 14:51.308
That's all right.

14:55.645 --> 14:56.938
Your turn.

14:58.815 --> 15:00.984
Then we can take our rightful
place in the melee.

15:16.750 --> 15:17.834
Sir Oswald!

15:21.213 --> 15:22.964
Didn't think you'd be brave
enough to show up.

15:23.048 --> 15:24.925
And miss the chance of putting you on
your backside?

15:25.008 --> 15:26.218
Ha-ha!

15:26.301 --> 15:29.179
-You've never managed it before.
-That was then. This is now.

15:31.348 --> 15:32.724
Sir Ethan.

15:34.643 --> 15:37.229
This is my servant Merlin.

15:38.480 --> 15:41.733
He loves hard work so,
anything you need, just give him a call.

15:41.817 --> 15:43.735
Believe me, I will.

15:46.696 --> 15:48.406
DAGR: Merlin!

15:52.452 --> 15:53.662
Here it is.

15:54.830 --> 15:56.081
-(GROANING)
-What took you so long?

15:56.164 --> 15:57.290
(THUDDING)

15:57.374 --> 15:59.501
(PANTING) What?

15:59.709 --> 16:01.545
It weighs a ton.

16:02.546 --> 16:05.048
The stairs, it's seven flights.

16:05.132 --> 16:07.384
That's very kind of you.

16:07.467 --> 16:09.052
(PANTING)

16:09.136 --> 16:10.512
But you can't leave it there.

16:10.595 --> 16:13.473
-I can't?
-It's in the way.

16:13.557 --> 16:15.308
Okay, where do you want it?

16:17.060 --> 16:18.895
Over there, by the bed.

16:20.313 --> 16:21.565
(SIGHING)

16:30.782 --> 16:33.910
Oh, no. The other side.

16:45.255 --> 16:47.299
It's going to get in my way there.

16:49.092 --> 16:50.427
Where do you want it?

16:50.510 --> 16:52.179
On top of the wardrobe.

16:52.262 --> 16:53.847
On top?

16:53.930 --> 16:57.934
You're absolutely right, Oswald.
That's exactly where it should be.

16:59.436 --> 17:01.062
(PANTING)

17:20.080 --> 17:21.875
(SLURPING)

17:25.127 --> 17:29.674
It's very hard to work out whether you
are eating or inhaling that soup.

17:29.758 --> 17:33.303
| haven't had anything all day.
Sir Oswald had me at his beck and call.

17:34.638 --> 17:35.889
How is he?

17:35.972 --> 17:38.475
Awful. He treats me like dirt.

17:38.558 --> 17:41.186
That doesn't sound like
the young man I knew.

17:41.269 --> 17:44.397
He always struck me as a
rather kind and thoughtful soul.

17:44.481 --> 17:45.941
He must have changed.

17:46.024 --> 17:50.487
You must remember that not all masters
are as good to their servants as Arthur.

17:56.993 --> 17:58.370
Thank you, Merlin.

18:00.080 --> 18:01.122
Sorry.

18:01.873 --> 18:03.041
(DOOR OPENING)

18:05.043 --> 18:07.170
Merlin, I think you need to
come with me.

18:16.763 --> 18:17.847
You drank all this?

18:17.931 --> 18:20.267
With some help from my new friends!

18:22.185 --> 18:24.312
He says that he hasn't got any money.

18:24.396 --> 18:27.065
So it looks like you'll have to pay.

18:27.148 --> 18:28.358
But... I can't afford this.

18:28.441 --> 18:30.485
You better find someone who can.

18:31.403 --> 18:33.405
(LAUGHS DRUNKENLY)

18:41.997 --> 18:43.790
You're the best friend I've ever had.

18:43.873 --> 18:45.208
You seem to have quite a few.

18:45.292 --> 18:47.502
(BOTH LAUGH)

18:47.585 --> 18:51.298
Oh, I'd love to see Arthur's face
when he gets that bill.

18:51.381 --> 18:52.799
Right.

18:52.882 --> 18:54.050
What is it with you and nobles?

18:54.175 --> 18:55.593
Oh, nothing.

18:55.677 --> 18:58.888
My father was a knight in
Caerleon's army.

18:58.972 --> 19:02.225
He died in battle,
leaving my mother penniless.

19:03.601 --> 19:07.022
And when she went to the King for help,
he turned her away.

19:09.649 --> 19:11.276
You didn't know him?

19:11.401 --> 19:13.486
Just some stories I've been told.

19:13.570 --> 19:15.196
Yeah, I know how that feels.

19:19.659 --> 19:22.746
| met my father just briefly
before he died.

19:22.871 --> 19:24.247
Why?

19:24.789 --> 19:26.207
He was banished.

19:27.042 --> 19:28.752
What had he done?

19:29.586 --> 19:30.754
Nothing.

19:34.299 --> 19:35.467
He served the King.

19:35.550 --> 19:37.093
But the King turned against him?

19:39.471 --> 19:41.264
That doesn't surprise me.

19:41.348 --> 19:42.849
-Arthur's not like that.
-(SCOFFS)

19:42.932 --> 19:46.186
Maybe. But none of them
are worth dying for, huh?

19:47.896 --> 19:50.273
(LAUGHING)

19:57.614 --> 19:59.657
Sorry. I know, I'm late.

19:59.908 --> 20:01.326
Not at all.

20:03.953 --> 20:04.996
Good.

20:05.622 --> 20:07.874
Sure you're all right? You're not sick,

20:07.957 --> 20:10.085
unsteady, about to burst into song?

20:10.168 --> 20:11.461
No, why?

20:16.007 --> 20:18.760
"Fourteen quarts of mead,

20:18.843 --> 20:21.805
â€œthree flagons of wine,
five quarts of cider..."

20:21.888 --> 20:22.931
| can explain.

20:23.014 --> 20:25.058
"Four dozen pickled eggs."

20:25.141 --> 20:26.226
That was Gwaine.

20:26.309 --> 20:28.353
He went to the tavern and, uh...

20:29.396 --> 20:30.688
He couldn't pay for it.

20:30.772 --> 20:32.690
So you said I would.

20:32.774 --> 20:33.983
Mmm.

20:34.067 --> 20:36.236
You know, if I hadn't, that innkeeper,

20:36.319 --> 20:37.946
he would've strung us both up.

20:38.029 --> 20:39.489
| fail to see the downside.

20:40.490 --> 20:42.117
You said he should be given
anything he needs.

20:42.200 --> 20:43.660
(SHOUTS) Four dozen pickled eggs?

20:43.743 --> 20:44.786
I'm sorry.

20:46.121 --> 20:47.163
I'll pay for it.

20:49.749 --> 20:52.502
You most certainly will.

20:52.585 --> 20:55.547
Arthur is a thoroughbred
little braggart.

20:55.630 --> 20:57.048
Why?

20:57.132 --> 20:58.842
For making us do this.

21:00.176 --> 21:02.011
| think it's fair.

21:03.304 --> 21:04.848
For the entire army?

21:08.476 --> 21:11.229
If you admitted your father was
a knight, you wouldn't have to.

21:11.312 --> 21:15.191
Maybe. But I'm not making the same
mistakes that he did.

21:15.316 --> 21:19.404
Anyway, my father
always treated his servants well.

21:21.656 --> 21:23.241
You didn't know him.

21:23.324 --> 21:24.951
Well, I like to think that he did.

21:28.204 --> 21:29.706
What about yours?

21:30.582 --> 21:32.876
No, he didn't have any servants.
He didn't have...

21:34.711 --> 21:36.504
Well, anyone.

21:37.297 --> 21:38.590
When did he die?

21:40.467 --> 21:43.344
About a year ago.
| just wish that I had the chance to

21:44.220 --> 21:45.805
know him better.

21:48.892 --> 21:50.727
So much he could've taught me.

21:52.687 --> 21:54.063
But you did get to meet him.

21:56.274 --> 21:57.817
Yeah.

21:58.776 --> 22:02.071
If there's one thing that
| learned from my father's life

22:02.155 --> 22:05.033
is that titles don't mean anything.

22:05.116 --> 22:07.660
It's what's inside that counts.

22:07.744 --> 22:08.745
Ow.

22:14.417 --> 22:16.711
You look like you need
a bit of practice.

22:17.587 --> 22:19.672
Ah, you think so?

22:19.756 --> 22:20.924
| kKnow soO.

22:26.846 --> 22:28.223
(SWORD SWISHING)

22:42.612 --> 22:44.656
You're rusty.
You're not as quick as you used to be.

22:44.739 --> 22:46.699
Still quick enough to hit you.

22:49.118 --> 22:51.120
| thought you were left-handed?

22:51.204 --> 22:52.747
Yes, I am, |I...

22:52.830 --> 22:55.500
Just wanted to give you a chance.

22:59.963 --> 23:01.798
Why don't we make this more interesting?

23:03.716 --> 23:05.552
50 gold coins first clean hit.

23:06.803 --> 23:08.596
Make it 100.

23:14.143 --> 23:15.520
You can keep your money.

23:22.527 --> 23:25.989
Don't worry, in the melee
there'll be two of us.

23:26.072 --> 23:28.783
And with the Stalorne blade
| will fillet the little brat.

24:07.447 --> 24:08.573
(CLINKING)

24:13.620 --> 24:15.204
What are you doing with that, boy?

24:16.205 --> 24:17.373
Uh...

24:19.876 --> 24:20.918
| was just tidying...

24:21.044 --> 24:23.046
Keep away from things
that don't concern you.

24:40.396 --> 24:43.566
To the eye the sword appeared blunt,
but when I touched it...

24:43.650 --> 24:47.695
You were lucky.
I've seen those blades in action.

24:47.779 --> 24:49.656
They're forged using sorcery.

24:49.739 --> 24:51.741
What would they want with such a blade?

24:51.824 --> 24:53.826
| think they mean to kill Arthur
in the melee.

24:53.910 --> 24:55.745
But in front of all those people?

24:55.828 --> 24:57.205
It's the perfect cover.

24:57.288 --> 25:00.291
If they succeed,
nobody will suspect it was intentional.

25:00.375 --> 25:01.417
| need to warn Arthur.

25:01.501 --> 25:04.504
Merlin, Sir Oswald's a knight.
He comes from a well-respected family.

25:04.587 --> 25:06.130
You can't accuse him without proof.

25:06.214 --> 25:08.633
-Then we need that blade.
-I'll get it.

25:09.884 --> 25:11.260
What if they catch you?

25:11.344 --> 25:14.472
What reason would you have to be in
Sir Oswald's chamber? No.

25:14.555 --> 25:16.557
It's safer if I do it.

25:22.146 --> 25:23.773
(SOFT SNORING)

25:37.078 --> 25:39.789
(CREAKING)

25:49.549 --> 25:50.967
(DAGR MUTTERING)

25:57.140 --> 26:00.768
(ENERGY PULSATING)

26:29.964 --> 26:31.924
Merlin should be back by now.

26:32.800 --> 26:33.885
| know.

26:34.886 --> 26:36.345
I'm going to go see what's going on.

26:39.640 --> 26:41.142
Gwaine!

26:44.145 --> 26:47.607
| was just rearranging the bedclothes,
that's all!

26:47.690 --> 26:51.486
You here that, Sir Ethan?
He was just rearranging the bedclothes.

26:51.569 --> 26:53.029
(DAGGER SWISHING)

26:53.196 --> 26:57.867
My mistake. He's not the
sniveling thief I thought he was.

26:59.744 --> 27:01.954
- I thought you might be cold!
-Of course you did.

27:02.747 --> 27:04.457
Is there a problem here?

27:05.792 --> 27:07.627
No. Now leave.

27:08.753 --> 27:10.129
-You all right, Merlin?
-No.

27:10.671 --> 27:12.381
| thought I told you to leave.

27:12.465 --> 27:13.966
| wasn't talking to you.

27:14.050 --> 27:16.594
How dare you speak to a
knight like that!

27:22.225 --> 27:23.726
Careful!

27:24.560 --> 27:27.897
Don't worry. I can handle this thug.

27:32.985 --> 27:34.570
(SHOUTING)

27:35.863 --> 27:37.698
Watch out!

27:44.539 --> 27:45.665
What's going on?

27:48.876 --> 27:50.461
This man attacked me!

27:50.753 --> 27:52.880
| demand an audience with the King!

27:53.172 --> 27:57.176
It's not Sir Oswald.
It's that thug from the tavern, Dagr.

27:57.260 --> 27:59.929
He's using a magical crystal
to change his appearance.

28:04.267 --> 28:06.936
Sire, this man attacked me,
with a sword,

28:07.687 --> 28:09.438
tried to kill me.

28:09.522 --> 28:10.982
Is this true?

28:11.065 --> 28:13.150
| stepped in to protect Merlin.

28:13.276 --> 28:17.029
| tried to talk to him.
He was like a man possessed.

28:17.113 --> 28:19.323
I'm sure that Sir Ethan will back me up.

28:19.448 --> 28:20.992
Indeed, I can vouch for his every word.

28:21.117 --> 28:22.243
He's a liar!

28:22.326 --> 28:26.956
| will have your tongue! How dare
you speak to a knight in that way?

28:27.123 --> 28:30.751
Nobility is defined by what you do

28:30.835 --> 28:33.671
and not by who you are.

28:33.754 --> 28:36.841
And these men are anything but.

28:37.550 --> 28:39.343
They are arrogant thugs!

28:39.427 --> 28:40.428
Gwaine.

28:40.511 --> 28:41.804
Well, you see, sire, how he behaves.

28:41.888 --> 28:43.472
UTHER: I've heard enough.

28:44.807 --> 28:48.644
For a commoner to attack a nobleman is
in violation of the Knight's Code.

28:48.728 --> 28:51.022
| couldn't agree with you more, sire.

28:51.105 --> 28:52.398
He must be made an example of.

28:52.481 --> 28:53.608
Sir Oswald, please.

28:53.691 --> 28:57.361
Nothing less than his execution
will give me satisfaction.

28:57.445 --> 29:01.657
Father, I understand how this must look,
it's an embarrassing situation.

29:01.782 --> 29:07.038
Sir Oswald is a dear friend
and our guest here in Camelot.

29:07.121 --> 29:10.041
But Gwaine is my guest here, too.

29:10.124 --> 29:12.877
And he may not be of noble birth, but
| can vouch that he has a noble heart.

29:12.960 --> 29:15.588
How can you say that when you
see the way he behaves?

29:15.671 --> 29:20.176
Gwaine risked his life to save mine.

29:22.303 --> 29:27.099
| beg you, please,
if a knight's word is his bond,

29:27.224 --> 29:32.355
then I give you my word.
Gwaine is a good man.

29:32.438 --> 29:34.106
He deserves clemency.

29:45.368 --> 29:48.454
You are banished from Camelot.

29:48.537 --> 29:51.290
If you ever return,
you will pay for it with your life.

29:52.375 --> 29:54.210
You have until dawn to leave the city.

30:04.512 --> 30:05.763
That servant boy is on to us.

30:05.846 --> 30:08.140
What's he gonna do?
We're knights, remember?

30:08.224 --> 30:10.935
You've seen what happens
when a commoner accuses a knight.

30:14.313 --> 30:15.648
I'm sorry.

30:15.731 --> 30:19.193
Don't be. I never stay in one place
for very long.

30:19.276 --> 30:21.654
-People get sick of me too quickly.
- I didn't.

30:21.737 --> 30:23.739
After the trouble I caused?

30:24.573 --> 30:26.617
-You livened the place up.
-(LAUGHING)

30:26.909 --> 30:29.161
Make sure you look after Arthur.

30:29.245 --> 30:30.287
He's in danger.

30:31.455 --> 30:32.873
| thought you hated nobles.

30:32.957 --> 30:36.752
Yeah, well, maybe that one's
worth dying for, eh?

30:49.348 --> 30:50.433
| heard what happened.

30:50.599 --> 30:52.727
Yeah, well, there you go.

30:53.227 --> 30:54.687
You did a brave thing.

30:55.104 --> 30:56.939
Hell of a lot of good it did me.

30:58.274 --> 31:01.610
| know Arthur. He's not like Uther.

31:03.195 --> 31:06.240
You saved his life, I'm sure one day
he'll repay you.

31:06.323 --> 31:08.367
He tried to speak up for me.

31:08.451 --> 31:11.037
Arthur's fair. He's loyal.

31:13.247 --> 31:14.874
He'll be a great king.

31:16.125 --> 31:17.501
| know he wiill.

31:18.669 --> 31:19.920
Clearly.

31:21.422 --> 31:24.050
If he makes everyone
feel the way that you do.

31:25.217 --> 31:28.179
At least now I know why
you turned me down.

31:28.387 --> 31:31.599
-It's not just me that says that.
-No, I'm sure it isn't.

31:32.266 --> 31:33.476
(SIGHING)

31:34.560 --> 31:35.895
Let's hope he lives that long.

31:41.108 --> 31:42.651
| don't know what we do.

31:43.069 --> 31:47.031
| could try and persuade Arthur to
withdraw from the contest.

31:47.114 --> 31:49.075
He won't. I know Arthur.

31:52.328 --> 31:54.163
I'll have to somehow...

31:55.998 --> 31:57.249
Use my powers to defend him.

31:59.043 --> 32:01.337
With the King and half
of Camelot watching?

32:01.837 --> 32:03.339
| don't have a choice.

32:13.349 --> 32:14.600
(DOOR OPENING)

32:15.935 --> 32:17.019
Ah.

32:21.023 --> 32:22.942
| trust you're ready for the challenge?

32:23.025 --> 32:24.193
Yes, Father.

32:24.360 --> 32:26.195
| came to bring you this.

32:26.779 --> 32:29.156
| won my first melee with this blade.

32:30.282 --> 32:32.660
The edge has been dulled,
it's perfectly safe.

32:34.370 --> 32:37.581
All of Camelot is eager
for a victory today, Arthur.

32:39.834 --> 32:41.418
| know you won't let me down.

33:12.199 --> 33:15.411
(TRUMPETS PLAYING)

33:20.291 --> 33:22.251
Prince Arthur isn't going to
know what's hit him.

33:22.334 --> 33:23.836
Oh, I hope he does.

33:23.919 --> 33:26.255
If it's over too quickly,
that'll be no fun at all.

33:26.547 --> 33:27.756
(CHUCKLES EVILLY)

33:32.094 --> 33:34.305
-Ready?
-Absolutely.

33:36.765 --> 33:40.186
You know those moments when I tell you
something isn't a good idea?

33:40.269 --> 33:41.979
And then I ignore you, yeah.

33:42.062 --> 33:43.939
And then I'm proved right?

33:44.064 --> 33:47.693
Merlin, your concern for my
well-being is touching.

33:47.776 --> 33:50.112
I'm serious.
| think you should withdraw.

33:52.156 --> 33:55.910
Look, I know you think the melee is
some Kind of stupid game.

33:58.495 --> 34:00.956
But it's more than that.

34:01.040 --> 34:03.792
It's about proving to the people that
I'm fit to lead them.

34:06.462 --> 34:07.463
| know.

34:12.384 --> 34:14.053
Just be careful.

34:19.683 --> 34:23.228
(CROWD CHEERING)

35:50.899 --> 35:52.568
MERLIN: He's heading straight
for Arthur.

36:19.136 --> 36:21.180
MERLIN: Arthur's in trouble.

36:42.159 --> 36:43.452
No!

36:56.548 --> 36:59.802
You'll have to do something.
Otherwise, Arthur will die.

37:23.700 --> 37:25.327
MERLIN: It's two against one.

37:46.348 --> 37:49.059
Who is that helping Arthur?

37:49.268 --> 37:52.729
| don't know, but I think
we should be thankful he is.

38:02.322 --> 38:05.033
There's only one person
| know who can do that.

38:08.203 --> 38:09.955
(CROWD EXCLAIMING)

38:30.058 --> 38:31.518
(CROWD GASPING)

38:45.407 --> 38:46.992
(PANTING)

38:47.743 --> 38:49.912
ARTHUR: They'll expect us to fight
to the end now.

39:07.930 --> 39:11.892
You fought bravely. The field is yours.

39:31.787 --> 39:33.247
| should've known.

39:36.708 --> 39:38.293
Nobody fights like you do.

39:49.096 --> 39:51.306
Guards! Seize him!

40:03.860 --> 40:05.571
Is there nothing you can do for them?

40:05.654 --> 40:07.489
I'm sorry, it's too late for them.

40:08.490 --> 40:12.286
The prisoner is responsible for their
deaths. I want him executed immediately.

40:12.369 --> 40:15.497
You might want to wait before
you pass judgment.

40:15.664 --> 40:17.082
| fear that...

40:18.667 --> 40:22.421
Sir Ethan and Sir Oswald

40:23.380 --> 40:25.048
are not all that they seem.

40:34.766 --> 40:36.268
Sorcery.

40:43.025 --> 40:45.027
And once again I owe Gwaine my life.

40:59.041 --> 41:01.668
The King is prepared to overlook the
fact that you fought in the melee.

41:01.752 --> 41:03.462
(GASPS) That's fantastic!

41:03.545 --> 41:05.672
-Thank you, Arthur.
-But...

41:07.341 --> 41:08.717
He's a stubborn man.

41:08.800 --> 41:12.054
He will not rescind his judgment.
You must leave Camelot.

41:12.929 --> 41:15.057
Oh, you've got to speak to him, Arthur,
make him change his mind.

41:15.140 --> 41:16.350
Merlin.

41:17.309 --> 41:20.354
I'm sorry, Gwaine. My father's wrong.

41:20.437 --> 41:22.064
-If it were up to me...
- I know.

41:22.189 --> 41:24.191
You don't need to explain yourself.

41:25.067 --> 41:26.652
You have until sunset.

41:28.737 --> 41:30.238
Where will you go?

41:30.322 --> 41:32.157
| was thinking Mercia.

41:32.240 --> 41:33.867
-It's dangerous.
-Yeah.

41:33.950 --> 41:36.036
And you get a lot more ale
for your money.

41:36.119 --> 41:37.496
I'm joking.

41:37.579 --> 41:39.414
Why don't you tell the King
who you really are?

41:39.498 --> 41:41.541
He'll grant you a pardon,
you can stay in Camelot.

41:41.625 --> 41:44.211
| could never serve under a
man like Uther.

41:44.294 --> 41:45.837
Yet you helped Arthur.

41:45.921 --> 41:48.090
-He stood up for me.
- I knew he would.

41:48.965 --> 41:50.342
That showed he is, indeed, a noble man.

41:50.425 --> 41:52.094
Then why don't you stay?

41:53.053 --> 41:55.847
You could be a knight. Like your father.

41:58.433 --> 42:01.478
You and Arthur,
you fought well together.

42:06.358 --> 42:08.110
Then maybe one day we will again.

42:26.461 --> 42:29.131
ARTHUR: It's a shame.
He would've been a great knight.

42:30.507 --> 42:32.217
Maybe one day he still will.

42:33.635 --> 42:35.637
The rules won't allow it.

42:35.721 --> 42:37.681
Knights are noblemen.

42:38.557 --> 42:40.392
Always have been, always will be.

42:40.475 --> 42:42.477
It's a tradition that...

42:49.151 --> 42:50.736
They seem very friendly!

42:50.819 --> 42:52.654
Why should you care?

42:55.490 --> 42:56.742
| don't.

42:56.825 --> 42:58.285
(GWEN LAUGHING)

42:59.786 --> 43:00.996
She could do better than that!

43:01.079 --> 43:03.749
What? She should be setting
her sights higher?

43:05.375 --> 43:10.088
Oh, but I forget! She can't.
A girl of Gwen's standing, no.

43:10.172 --> 43:13.008
She could never consort with a nobleman.
That's the rules.

43:13.925 --> 43:16.261
-Merlin.
-Shut up.

43:17.179 --> 43:18.555
You guessed it.

43:34.237 --> 43:35.864
Merlin.

43:39.117 --> 43:40.952
This is the Crystal Cave.

43:41.036 --> 43:43.205
Use what you see for good.

43:43.330 --> 43:44.372
No!

43:44.456 --> 43:46.291
| can't get these visions
out of my head.

43:46.374 --> 43:48.293
The events I saw are imminent.

43:48.376 --> 43:50.545
Morgana, is going to kill Uther.

43:55.217 --> 43:56.968
We have to stop her.

43:59.721 --> 44:00.722
(SCREAMS)
